[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(21) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "It had been better for them not to have known.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—There are many things of which the well-known lines.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“’Tis better to have loved and lost,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Than never to have loved at all,”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "do not hold good. To have loved a great truth, to have loved a high principle, and after all to lose them, is what often causes the shipwreck of a life. To have loved Jesus Christ and lost Him is to make shipwreck of eternal life.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The way of righteousness.—The life of the Christian. That which from a doctrinal point of view is “the way of truth” (2Peter 2:2), from a moral point of view is “the way of righteousness.” So also “the faith delivered to the saints” of Jude 1:3, is the doctrinal equivalent of “the holy commandment delivered unto them” of this verse.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The way of righteousness.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The life of the Christian. That which from a doctrinal point of view is “the way of truth” (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Peter 2:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "), from a moral point of view is “the way of righteousness.” So also “the faith delivered to the saints” of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jude 1:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", is the doctrinal equivalent of “the holy commandment delivered unto them” of this verse.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2:17-22 The word of truth is the water of life, which refreshes the souls that receive it; but deceivers spread and promote error, and are set forth as empty, because there is no truth in them. As clouds hinder the light of the sun, so do these darken counsel by words wherein there is no truth. Seeing that these men increase darkness in this world, it is very just that the mist ofdarkness should be their portion in the next. In the midst of their talk of liberty, these men are the vilest slaves; their own lusts gain a complete victory over them, and they are actually in bondage. When men are entangled, they are easily overcome; therefore Christians should keep close to the word of God, and watch against all who seek to bewilder them. A state of apostacy is worse than a state of ignorance. To bring an evil report upon the good way of God, and a false charge against the way of truth, must expose to the heaviest condemnation. How dreadful is the state here described! Yet though such a case is deplorable, it is not utterly hopeless; the leper may be made clean, and even the dead may be raised. Is thy backsliding a grief to thee? Believe in the Lord Jesus, and thou shalt be saved.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For it had been better for them ... - Compare the notes at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It would have been better for them, for:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(1) then they would not have dishonored the cause of religion as they have now done;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) they would not have sunk so deep in profligacy as they now have; and,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(3) they would not have incurred so aggravated a condemnation in the world of woe. If people are resolved on being wicked, they had better never pretend to be good. If they are to be cast off at last, it had better not be as apostates from the cause of virtue and religion. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(3) they would not have incurred so aggravated a condemnation in the world of woe. If people are resolved on being wicked, they had better never pretend to be good. If they are to be cast off at last, it had better not be as apostates from the cause of virtue and religion. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "21. the way of righteousness—\"the way of truth\" (2Pe 2:2). Christian doctrine, and \"the knowledge of the Lord and Saviour.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "turn—back again; so the Greek.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "from the holy commandment—the Gospel which enjoins holiness; in opposition to their corruption. \"Holy,\" not that it makes holy, but because it ought to be kept inviolate [Tittmann].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "delivered—once for all; admitting no turning back.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "It had been better for them not to have known; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " their sin had been less if they had not known the truth, but now they sin against knowledge, and therein their apostacy is much worse than their ignorance would have been. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "The way of righteousness; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the way of obtaining righteousness by Christ, and of living godly in Christ, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Timothy 3:12",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Timothy 3:12",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", prescribed in the gospel; the same which is called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the right way, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " 2 Peter 2:15",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Peter 2:15",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the way of truth, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " 2 Peter 2:2",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Peter 2:2",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "The holy commandment; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the same in other words. It is called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "holy, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " not only as proceeding from God, who is holy, but as teaching nothing but what is holy, and being the means God useth in making men holy, and as being opposed to the pollutions of the world before mentioned. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
