  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Peter 2:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κρεῖττον γὰρ ἦν αὐτοῖς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The same use of the imperf. where we should employ the conjunct., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καλὸν ἦν αὐτῷ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; cf. on the constr. Winer, p. 265 [E. T. 352].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μὴ ἐπεγνωκέναι τὴν ὁδὸν τῆς δικαιοσύνης",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἡ ὁδὸς τῆς δικαιοσ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". is not: “the way to virtue,” or “the way of salvation which leads to the moral condition of righteousness” (Schott), but a designation of Christianity in so far as a godly righteous life belongs to it; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Peter 2:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".[82]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἤ ἐπιγνοῦσιν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The dat. instead of the accus., dependent on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αὐτοις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; by an attraction not uncommon in Greek.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐπιστρέψαι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] is to be taken here in the sense of: “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to turn back to the former things",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ";” cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Peter 2:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 13:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 17:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where it is connected with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰς τὰ ὀπίσω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
